  "assembler_notes": {
    "recommended": "Use NASM with Intel mnemonics (cpu 186 mode) for the 8086/80186-compatible subset; encode NEC-only instructions with db/macros.",
    "gotchas": [
      "NEC 'INS' (bit-field insert) is NOT Intel INS (port input string); NEC calls the latter INM.",
      "NEC 'MUL' is Intel IMUL; NEC unsigned multiply is MULU. Same pattern for DIV/DIVU.",
      "NEC 'BP' is a branch (JNS), which collides with the register name BP in Intel syntax.",
      "Undocumented/undefined opcodes differ from 8086: V-series has no 8086 aliases like SALC/SETMO behavior; unknown opcodes have V-series-specific behavior (to be measured)."
    ]
  }
